Unfortunately, the offer of the operators is miserable and is usually limited to hits of the moment of the radio.
The prices are not very low.
But it is generally assumed that this mode of selling music (be it via GSM, internet or wireless internet) will dominate the music industry in the future.
Most people always carry their phones.
Anyone who wants to listen to something rummages in their pocket while the MP3 player is forgotten at home.
But it also depends on this, whether you always carry the headphones or at least the wireless headset.
If not, you can use the built-in player that almost every mobile phone, but only a small part of MP3 players, has.
Perhaps the biggest advantage of mobile readers will be, for many, the price.
