Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be written in the history of the Prague Transport Company as the date on which the first passengers who will have an electronic card in their pocket will go up in the metro, tramway and bus.
At this time they can get it about one hundred thousand people who own their Opencard card.
Passengers can buy the 30- and 90-day and annual one (which will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have their card recharged in the Infopoints and offices of the Transport Company and at the metro stop Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská Zahrada,
The coupons can be bought as early as yesterday on the internet at the page of the Transport Company www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred customers took advantage of the service before the afternoon.
Those who will start using the service via the internet can completely forget the counters in the metro stops where so far they had to make long lines for paper tickets.
The coupon is bought via the internet and on the Opencard they recharge it on one of the twelve branches of the Municipal Library.
"In these places passengers have at their disposal a counter with trained staff who will help those interested in buying on the internet and will also register on their card the credit acquired." said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
