The rocky Graziano boxer, delinquent, tormented, violent, unforgettable in Up there someone loves me, by Robert Wise, a role destined for James Dean and resumed after his death, which officially launched Newman in 1956.
That cute thug in the excellent Stangata, Oscar for best picture in 1973.
Bitter and vindictive pool player in The Slot, magnificent film by Robert Rossen (1961), The Color of Money by Martin Scorsese, which earned him in 1987 the only Oscar for 9 nominations.
