What was produced in the Zuschlag invoice factory & associates?
Soon, on 8 October, the hearing of the criminal trial against János Zuschlag and associates will be discussed.
The politician and his associates are accused of repeated commercial fraud committed as part of a criminal association that has caused considerable damage, and other crimes, including falsification of documents.
According to the Prosecutor's Office, the money obtained from notices of competition, was used by them for private purposes, and they often certified the execution of activities through false invoices.
State and municipal money, a total of 65 million guilders, ended up partly in the coffers of the Fiatal Baloldal organization, partly in the pockets of some people.
According to the method, made known by the investigating authorities, they have withdrawn the money obtained from notices of competition on the basis of invoices for non-existent transactions and the associations have never fulfilled the obligations assumed.
According to the accusatory act, most of the invoices were false.
To do them, the invoice blocks were purchased at the Józsefváros market, while the circular stamps were manufactured in Kiskunhalas.
And to decide on behalf of which companies to issue invoices, it was established among other things during the trip through the hills above the Balaton where János Zuschlag had sent István Lados.
According to the latter's confession he had to choose pensions and restaurants.
He asked for an invoice for the consumptions, on the model of these then were prepared the invoices to be forwarded to the notices of competition, among others, to those of the Ministry for Youth and Sport, the Ministry of Labor and Social Affairs and the Municipality of Budapest.
Most of these are the work of István Lados and András Őri who, according to our information, has drawn up above all the reports necessary to obtain the funding.
One of the choices of Lados's "journey studies" was a brewery.
According to two invoices issued by Zuschlag and members in 2003, the place of catering provided meals for a group of 90 people of the Biztos Pont Egyesület Association.
So many people, however, according to the restaurateur, would not all enter the restaurant together.
Similarly, the invoice issued in summer 2002 to the Jobb Jövőért Foundation, hereinafter referred to as Együtt in Harmadik Évezredért, is full of formal and content errors.
A pension in Badacsonytomaj has only three rooms, more than 10 people could not stay overnight, however 130 guests were in the invoice.
But the compilers of the invoices full of imagination exaggerated when they reported the Pigal Kft., also this deals with catering, in whose accounting - according to the information issued to the judicial authorities - did not even appear the documents on behalf of the companies Jobb Jövőért and Hoppá.
Győző Farkas, the company's administrator, told hvg.hu that when he was summoned to the prosecutor's office and they showed him the invoices, he quickly realised that it was fake documents.
"On the stamp the name and VAT number of our enterprise were in the wrong place."
He added: in addition to the formal reasons, the fact that according to the invoice a hundred people were accommodated, when in total they have eleven rooms and there are not so many beds.
In addition, the invoice was catering and their restaurant has not been in operation for a long time.
The regular invoice compilers did not bother to inquire that the Budapest travel agency of their choice, only organizes trips abroad, so they foolishly indicated on the invoice with cash payment travel to Hungary, which did not agree with the company's invoices practice.
In addition, as demonstrated during the survey, VAT was also included on the invoice, while the activity of travel to countries outside the European Union is exempt from VAT.
Among other things, the amount of VAT was also incorrect on the four documents issued by the Hotel Révfülöp Kft. in favor of the Jobb Jövőért foundation, in fact, on the services offered by the company it is necessary to apply VAT at 15% and not 25% as indicated on the invoices, moreover the employees of the hotel issued only printed invoices, while the invoice was written by hand.
In addition to this, the "issuers" have ruined other invoices, in the case of a company they have indicated as activity carried out the transport of goods by road, as it is known from the procedure of the Public Prosecutor's Office, activities that was not carried out by the company originally founded for investment advice.
Moreover, for formal defects - cause non-compliant invoice format, false stamp - it was discovered that the invoices issued in favour of Együtt in Harmadik Évezredért Alapítvány, of XXI. Századi Kulturális Egyesület and Biztos Pont are fake.
The same happened in the case of Ravenna Bt. or the Kunfehértó Sports Field, whose representatives denied issuing the invoices in question.
The falsifiers did not even pay attention to the fact that the HIB Kft. of Nyíregyháza was in liquidation when (2001) a group of Fiatal Városért Egyesület had lunch, for this reason the administrator of the company's liquidation, according to our information, denied that he had issued that invoice.
They have issued invoices knowingly
Another group of invoice broadcasters consists of those who were aware that they had to issue fictitious invoices.
The Esély Budapestért Alapítány Foundation issued an invoice at the request of Fiatal Baloldal - Ifjú Szocialisták in favour of the Együtt foundation in Harmadik Évezredért of almost 4 million guilders.
Ludovic Györfi, one of the defendants, according to the accusatory act, persuaded the director of the Collab Kft. to issue fictitious invoices.
The Biogate Kft currently in liquidation, which in 2003 provided invoices issued for a value of about 5 million guilders to the Jobb Jövőért Alapítány Foundation, the Atlasz Egyesület association and the Vörösfenyő Egyesület association, behind which there was no real economic activity
Not even a movement of money because the prepared invoices were then reversed, but the associations forgot to show this aspect in their documents.
In the following group of companies issuing invoices belong those who are connectable with the defendants.
E.g. Ivan Kubatov, authorized to deliver the general manager of the Delta Trió Kft, based in Budapest but not available there, which deals with fuel and motor vehicle trade.
The company released several invoices in October, November and December 2005 relating to the sale of IT means, worth about 18 million guilders.
According to the data of the investigation, the Cash Investment Kft. of Kiskunhalas under liquidation since 14 September 2005 has purchased these invoices.
The director-general of this company was a Romanian to whom Ivan Kubatov submitted documents concerning the company between 2002 and 2005.
As far as we know Kubatov, during the investigation, acknowledged that he had issued invoices in the name of the company to the companies Atlasz, Hoppá and Együtt in Harmadik Évezredért Alapítvány and the countervalue was taken from him.
