However, the companies came in handy because at the request of the co-defendant lawyer Zsolt Szente, editor of the foundation documents of the companies, in the name of the companies, invoices were issued to the associations linked to Zuschlag: the Atlasz and the Y-Generáció.
On behalf of the Cash Investment companies, Delta Trió, Fa-Bani Jos, Jos Investment and Linaxtrade Kubatov released 15 invoices to the various institutions for a total value of 14.2 million guilders.
The prosecutors believe that Kubatov has pocketed 10% of the amounts indicated on the invoices, as well as VAT.
The man also used the Szi-Beri Bt. to issue fictitious invoices, manufactured for the Biztos Pont competition notice.
