According to the result of a recent survey, religious faith functions as a kind of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
Scientists at the University of Oxford have performed an interesting experiment, examining how faith in god affects the sensation of pain, the British Telegraph said.
As part of the rather bizarre investigation, an electroshock was carried out to 12 Catholic believers and to as many atheists, while all those observed a painting depicting the virgin Mary.
According to the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
